Conclusion
Docker Image, Dockerfile, and Docker Hub are core components of Docker. The Dockerfile defines how an image is built, the image is the final packaged application, and Docker Hub is used to store and distribute these images. Together, they enable efficient, portable, and scalable application deployment in DevOps environments.
