•	Shows how much code is tested 
•	Helps identify untested parts of the application 
________________________________________
2. Improves Code Quality
•	Encourages developers to write better test c
•	Reduces bugs in production 
________________________________________
3. Identifies Untested Code
•	Highlights missing test coverage 
•	Helps improve test completeness 
________________________________________
4. Supports CI/CD Pipeline
•	Integrated with tools like Jenkins, Maven, Gradle 
•	Automatically checks coverage during build process 
________________________________________
5. Helps in Regression Testing
•	Ensures new changes do not break existing functionality 
________________________________________
